    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it wasn't just a \"maybe.\" it was so specific. like, the ringing was at a certain pitch and then immediately after, the volatility spiked. if it's just coincidence, why does it happen every time there's a major move? it's like my body is catching the signal before it even hits the screens. could there be some kind of electromagnetic field interaction that science just hasn't mapped out yet?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
